dismissalText.long: c Shubman Gill b Kuldeep Yadav
dismissalText.commentary: Ben Duckett c Shubman Gill b Kuldeep Yadav 27 (58b 4x4 0x6 88m) SR: 46.55

dismissalComment.html: skied to cover, well held! Kuldeep gets the breakthrough in his first over. Tossed up and Duckett's eyes are wide as he looks to launch over the leg side, only to get a b-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-i-g leading edge. Shubman Gill has to turn and scurry back a good 20 yards but makes the ground and holds on to a diving catch. Spin does the job for India on a morning for the seamers

dismissalText.commentary: Ollie Pope st †Jurel b Kuldeep Yadav 11 (24b 0x4 0x6 29m) SR: 45.83

dismissalComment.html: comes down and strung up, Jurel completes the stumping! Kuldeep foxes Pope with the googly and plucks out a second wicket on the stroke of lunch! India can walk off feeling a tad bit more satisfied with their work this morning. Pope was nowhere near the ball as it skidded on with the angle from over the wicket. He threw his head back in frustration, another low score to add to his collection in India

Rod Tucker raises his finger again and India have two in four balls
